        <name xml:lang="en">bromopropane</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value based on stoichiometric calculations and literature data. 
122.99258g/mol is the molar mass of bromopropane (C3H7Br). 
326.43564g/mol is the molar mass of octabenzone (C21H26O3). 

The production of octabenzone is modelled here as the reaction of 2,4-dihydroxy-2 benzophenone, 1-bromo-octane, acetone and potassium carbonate. Acetone is not included in the inventory as it is assumed that solvents are closed-loop recycled (ChemYQ, n.d.).</comment>
